b"This is exactly why Jorginho is if not the most, one of the most important players for Chelsea we simply can't function without him. We have maintained 18 unbeaten games with him starting."

b'And Jorginho is unarguably the best in the world at those aspects of the game. We are toothless possession wise without him.The moment we lose our tempo setter and the player who keeps our possession intact we lose our entire mid field.'

b'Hence, Jorginho has inclined and adapted to the role that Tuchel has given to him quickly, (sitting deeper/cutting through shorter passes instead of long balls/ and being a defensive ball circulator) Which results in us having more possession.'

b'Playing Jorginho deeper allows us to spend more time in the final third too, it allows us to play in the penalty box more as well. We\xe2\x80\x99ve looked exceptionally well in this regard, whilst having Jorginho in the deeper role: https://t.co/nJKDHdhJ9t'

b'Tuchel is using his wingbacks to maintain build-up play.  Kova has taken the job of progressing the ball up very well too.Therefore crucifying jorginho for the lack of ball progression is unreasonable. Because he\xe2\x80\x99s been the best in the league alongside Rodri otherwise: https://t.co/vOtVhAAngZ'

b'however he\xe2\x80\x99s been placed as a defensive ball circulator under tuchel. In our current set up, jorginho\xe2\x80\x99s primarily role is not of being a ball progress-or because we\xe2\x80\x99ve been progressing the ball more through wider channels rather centrally (wide CBS and WBS) hence key highlighting'

b'City did it exceptionally, they locked down jorginho\xe2\x80\x99s passing lanes, pressed him high and that made us lose control of the game.  \nWe have seen that his role was more fluid and attacking under Lampard,'

b'The 7-0 Norwich game is another example how players leave Jorginho free and try to press our midfield and CBs instead. you need to press jorgi instead and the lanes he uses to make passes. We fold easily then.'

b"Maintained possession, didn't lose the ball, and settled the pace and tempo of the game (3 passes into final third - Joint 2nd\n2 shots blocked - 2nd).Jorginho is exceptional  positionally and also picks out very effective passes from anywhere on the field."

b'Jorginho was subbed on and we took control of the game back quickly.(46th minute substitution ) \xe2\x80\x93 Stabilised Chelsea\xe2\x80\x99s game in possession, allowing Kova\xc4\x8di\xc4\x87 to push forward more. The team\xe2\x80\x99s performance became a lot more coherent with his arrival.'

b'When the player who is supposed to do that doesn\xe2\x80\x99t do it well, the mid-field gets outrun, then the team doesn\xe2\x80\x99t have those easy passes and they rush longer passes or make passes that are not simple. Another key example is where Jorginho was rested and Saul started the Villa game.'

b'Our Brentford game is a perfect example of how Jorginho could\xe2\x80\x99ve helped us maintain the pace and tempo of the game. We rushed through passes and the player who is the key focus of receiving those passes wasn\xe2\x80\x99t present hence we kept losing the ball.'

b'One of his biggest strengths is making passes under pressure. In this aspect, Jorginho is one of the best in the league. (97th-98th% for forward passes under pressure) his line-breaking passes are needed in our build-up and helps in breaking the opponent\xe2\x80\x99s press. https://t.co/Jgw62rFmTG'
